# tourbillon / backups orchestration on kodiak.
#
# After ADR-004 (kodiak-side service user), the A2 cron entries (repos sync,
# hosts sync) moved to the tourbillon user's crontab. What's left on ldavis
# is monitoring — saratoga DR replication freshness checks + monthly host
# restore drills. Cron failure mail forwards to the operator's external
# gmail via msmtp (see ~ldavis/.msmtprc; CREDENTIALS.md for rotation).
MAILTO=lynchdavis0@gmail.com

# Daily 08:00 — alert if saratoga's ZFS replication hasn't landed a fresh
# snapshot in the last 26h. Silent on success.
0 8 * * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/check-saratoga-replication.sh

# Monthly restore-drill — verifies backup integrity for each host
# end-to-end (mirror hash == source hash == reverse-rsync'd hash).
# Silent on success; cron mails any FAILED check via MAILTO=ldavis.
# Add one line per host as the fleet grows.
30 6 1 * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/restore-drill.sh arrow-iii
35 6 1 * * /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/tests/restore-drill.sh pilatus

# Weekly summary — Sunday 08:00. Self-mails via msmtp with a useful
# Subject line ("kodiak weekly backup summary YYYY-MM-DD"), so cron's
# default "Cron <ldavis@kodiak> ..." subject isn't what lands in gmail.
# Acts as a heartbeat: if no email arrives some Sunday, monitoring
# itself is broken (different failure mode from "everything's fine").
0 8 * * 0 /home/ldavis/development/server-backups/bin/weekly-summary.sh
